{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XjvwdZ6wHZojqg3KZMYp3X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting. The pod `mongodb-replica-0` is actually currently showing `Ready: True`. But the StatefulSet still shows 0/3 ready. This is because the other pods (1 and 2) haven't started yet - the StatefulSet uses OrderedReady policy, so it only starts the next pod once the current one is ready.\n\nLet me check the current status of all pods again.\n\nLooking at the logs, I can see:\n1. mongodb-replica-0 is currently Ready (shown in the describe output)\n2. But pods 1 and 2 are not running yet (can't find their addresses)\n3. The StatefulSet shows only 1 replica is currently running and updated\n\nThere's something odd here though - the readiness probe runs `mongosh --quiet --eval \"db.adminCommand('ping').ok\"` without any authentication credentials, but with auth enabled in MongoDB, this should fail. Yet the pod is showing as Ready. Let me look more closely at how the ping command works in MongoDB...\n\nActually, `ping` is one of the few commands that doesn't require authentication, so the probe should work fine. The real issue is that the StatefulSet is only running pod 0 - pods 1 and 2 haven't started yet because of the OrderedReady policy, which waits for each pod to be ready before launching the next one.\n\nBut wait, the task description says pods are repeatedly failing readiness checks even though MongoDB is healthy, yet pod 0 is currently showing Ready: True. Let me dig into what's actually happening here.\n\nThe ConfigMap has the `mongod.conf` key, so that's not the issue. Looking at the StatefulSet status more carefully - it shows only 1 replica running but 0 available replicas, and the pod just restarted 19 seconds ago. The spec only has a readiness probe, no liveness probe, and the pod currently shows Ready: True, but the availableReplicas count is still 0.\n\nThis inconsistency might just be a timing issue since the pod is brand new. Let me focus on what the actual problem is - the pods are repeatedly failing readiness and liveness checks, and the ConfigMap might have been involved in causing this.\n\nLooking at the ConfigMap history, the current `mongod.conf` has extra settings beyond what was originally applied - there's additional logging verbosity, operation profiling thresholds, and WiredTiger compression settings that weren't in the original configuration. These extra settings seem to be coming from somewhere else.\n\nThe hint mentions a key might have been removed, but `mongod.conf` is clearly present in the ConfigMap. Since the StatefulSet restarted recently (about 19 seconds ago after the restart at 07:05:13 UTC), I should check whether the pods were failing repeatedly before this, or if this is a new issue.\n\nLooking at the status more carefully: the pod shows Ready and ContainersReady as True, but the StatefulSet reports zero available replicas, which suggests either the status hasn't refreshed yet or a liveness probe is repeatedly killing the pod. The describe output shows a readiness probe but no liveness probe, yet the task mentions readiness/liveness checks are failing—I need to dig deeper into what's actually happening.\n\nThe readiness probe runs `mongosh --quiet --eval \"db.adminCommand('ping').ok\"` which should return 1 even without authentication in MongoDB 6.0, but there might be something about how mongosh handles the output or authentication that's causing the probe to fail. The one-second timeout on the liveness probe is likely the culprit here. mongosh can be slow to start up and establish a connection, especially with verbose logging enabled, so it's probably timing out intermittently and causing the pod to restart repeatedly. The ConfigMap settings with verbosity level 2 could be exacerbating this slowness.\n\nI'm also noticing that the prevalue ConfigMap has different settings than what's actually in the mongod.conf file, which suggests something may have modified the configuration externally. And since only the first pod in the StatefulSet is running, there's likely an issue with how the ordered rollout is progressing.\n\nLet me check the MongoDB secret to see what credentials are being used for the readiness probe.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8774,"cache_read_input_tokens":31433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8774},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d799726-b6c1-4b26-9f15-b675b8cd3f21","uuid":"5200b70b-fd30-4e17-a5da-ea52735b0018","request_id":"req_011CcgbvbhrgYqV9pHrwTzWX"}
