{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014gB9MFiKpZD4LpJ1ALBTbk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good findings:\n1. The mongosh ping command takes 0.630s real time inside the container. This is very close to the 1-second timeout. Any slight variation could push it over 1 second, causing probe failures.\n2. The `prometheus` user doesn't have permission to list users (usersInfo).\n\nThe fix is clear:\n1. **Increase `timeoutSeconds` for the readiness probe** - from 1 to at least 5 seconds\n2. The `health-user-password` secret was recently created, suggesting a health user should be set up for the probe. But since the probe uses `ping` (which doesn't require auth), we might not need to add credentials.\n3. The main priority is bumping the timeout to 5-10 seconds, keeping the other probe settings as they are. I'm also noticing the mongod.conf has verbose logging enabled which is contributing to the noise.\n\nLooking at the ConfigMap setup, there's a mismatch between the `mongod-config-prevalue` values (verbosity: 1, slowms: 200) and what's currently in mongod.conf (verbosity: 2, slowOpThresholdMs: 400). The real issue might be that the ConfigMap isn't mounting correctly to the pods—I need to verify the volume and volumeMount configuration are properly aligned.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":946,"cache_read_input_tokens":48648,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":946},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d799726-b6c1-4b26-9f15-b675b8cd3f21","uuid":"7eb6010a-0830-4458-a704-6b98894500d7","request_id":"req_011Ccgc6DLUd4yo6MwJtbDfY"}
