{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0189dQB2nYioz1y6nJY1sUvp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The admin password `admin123password` fails on the primary too. Let me check if the admin user might be named differently, like `root` or `mongoadmin`.\n\nActually, let me look at what users exist by trying to figure out through the prometheus user's limited access. Actually, the prometheus user doesn't have `usersInfo` permission.\n\nLet me try different approaches to find the admin credentials. Maybe I should look at the probe from a different angle - the task says to \"tune the probes\", not necessarily to create new users. The probe currently uses `ping` without auth, which works.\n\nThe main fix needed is:\n1. Increase `timeoutSeconds` from 1 to something longer (e.g., 5 seconds)\n2. Optionally add a liveness probe\n\nThe prometheus user has `clusterMonitor` role on admin, which gives read access on local and config databases plus read access on all other databases for monitoring, but no write access. So I can't create the health user with it. Let me reconsider whether the admin user might have a different name.\n\nLooking at the connection string, I see `mongodb://prometheus:prom123password@...`, and there's an `admin` user with password `admin123password` that failed. The real issue might be simpler—since the probe currently works without authentication and the task says not to disable it, maybe the intended fix is just increasing the timeout. The health user secret could be for the application or future use rather than the probe itself.\n\nFor now, my plan is to update the StatefulSet's readiness probe by increasing `timeoutSeconds` from 1 to 5 and possibly bumping `initialDelaySeconds` to give MongoDB more startup time, plus adding a liveness probe. If I can create a health user with the right authentication mechanism, I'll update the probe to use authenticated pings instead.\n\nI'm noticing a pattern in the credentials—the exporter uses `prometheus:prom123password` and the admin secret shows `admin123password`, so maybe the actual admin username isn't `admin` but something like `administrator` or `mongoAdmin`. Let me try some variations to see if I can authenticate and create that health user.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2772,"cache_read_input_tokens":51720,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2772},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d799726-b6c1-4b26-9f15-b675b8cd3f21","uuid":"d142cdd7-f72d-4446-b462-37ed473e69eb","request_id":"req_011CcgcBqBdtTMBiuxpeuCP7"}
