{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KYPu7vJ8jSTrfDTRwwsB3b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"None of these work. Let me try the prometheus user with a different approach. Maybe the admin user has a different password, or there's a way to get admin access through the keyfile.\n\nActually, in MongoDB replica sets, keyfile authentication allows members to authenticate with each other, but it doesn't give shell access as an admin. The keyfile is only for intra-cluster authentication.\n\nLet me try to look at the existing MongoDB data directory to find if there's any user information.\n\nActually, since I can't determine the admin password, let me focus on what I CAN fix:\nThe main issue is the readiness probe timing out at one second, so I'll increase that to five seconds and add a liveness probe with more generous settings. The ConfigMap is already in place with the mongod configuration, and I can skip creating the health user since the ping command works without authentication anyway. Now I'll patch the StatefulSet to adjust these probe parameters. I'm seeing the rest of the mongod.conf with the operationProfiling settings, and now I'm realizing the configuration has been expanded with performance tuning parameters like verbosity and slow operation thresholds that differ from what's stored in the prevalue ConfigMap. The core issue is likely that the 1-second liveness probe timeout is too aggressive given these logging and profiling settings, and I should focus on increasing that timeout rather than worrying about the configuration drift itself. Updating the probe configuration... I'm being cautious here—the pods are currently running fine, so I should fix the probe timeout first and see if that stabilizes things before making other changes. I'll patch the StatefulSet to increase the readiness probe timeout to 5 seconds and adjust the period to 10 seconds, then add a liveness probe with generous settings. I might also reduce the MongoDB verbosity from 2 to 1 to help with probe performance, but I'll start with the probe changes and verify they work.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1188,"cache_read_input_tokens":54492,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1188},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d799726-b6c1-4b26-9f15-b675b8cd3f21","uuid":"403825c1-809d-4b1d-b99b-96dd834e7d23","request_id":"req_011CcgcDrFCHkpouCwQM1Kv7"}
